-- Oakley Capital Said to Close Fund of Hedge Funds in Commodities
-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r o w n
-- 2013-10-29T14:50:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-29/oakley-capital-said-to-close-fund-of-hedge-funds-in-commodities.html
Oakley Capital Management Ltd.
closed its commodities fund of hedge funds as a gauge of
performance across the industry retreated for a third year,
according to two people with direct knowledge.  The London-based fund shut in July and Portfolio Manager
Fabio Cortes left the company at about the same time, said the
people, who asked not to be identified because the information
is private. The fund managed $10 million of assets, one of the
people said. An e-mail seeking comment sent to a LinkedIn Corp.
account in Cortes’ name on Oct. 25 wasn’t answered.  The Newedge Commodity Trading Index, which tracks 56 hedge
funds that buy and sell raw materials, fell 1 percent in the
first nine months, extending two years of losses. Prices for
everything from industrial and precious metals to grains and
gasoline dropped this year as supply outpaced demand.  Clive Capital LLP, the $1 billion commodity hedge fund
based in  London , told clients it would shut at the end of last
month after more than two years of losses. It lost 9.1 percent
this year through Sept. 18, according to a letter to investors
obtained by Bloomberg News.  Oakley is an asset management and financial advisory
business which manages more than $1 billion of assets, including
the Oakley Absolute Return Fund and the Oakley Opportunities
Fund, according to data on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
